          "NYC presents unique lighting opportunities that ground-level suburban properties simply cannot offer. A terrace 20 stories above Midtown can use subtle uplighting to frame skyline views while keeping the seating area comfortably dim. A brownstone garden can use path lights and wall washers to create a glowing pocket of warmth visible from the kitchen window. Commercial facades can use architectural lighting to stand out on crowded streetscapes. The possibilities are as varied as the city's properties.",
          "Landscaping In NYC designs and installs landscape lighting systems using premium low-voltage LED fixtures rated for the harsh conditions of the NYC environment — salt air, freeze-thaw cycles, high winds, and constant exposure. Our lighting designs are integrated into the overall landscape plan, not added as an afterthought, which ensures that fixture placement, wiring routes, and transformer locations are planned for optimal effect and minimal visual clutter.",
