          "Downlighting (moonlighting) mounts fixtures high in trees or on overhead structures to cast a natural, dappled light pattern that mimics moonlight filtering through branches. This technique is particularly effective in larger gardens and Westchester estate properties where mature trees provide natural mounting points. String lights and festoon lighting create a casual, inviting atmosphere for outdoor dining areas and are among the most requested features for Brooklyn backyard gardens and restaurant patios.",
